message.content: cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.COMM, cs.SY - This paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of a new congestion control algorithm for the Internet, which falls under the category of network protocols and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also touches upon issues related to security and fairness, which could place it in the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could place it in the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.COMM (Computer Communication and Networks).
